<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-88-0156 </DOCNO><TEXT>We discuss the squeezing of vacuum fluctuations by resonant interactionwith a suitably prepared atom. We demonstrate the crucial role of atomicdipole fluctuations in modifying the vacuum noise. We show how the generationof field squeezing in spontaneous and fluorescent processes is dependenton the squeezing of the atomic dipole.</TEXT></DOC>